{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e292c7d4-9eba-4ae0-8a04-a935cf846afc","content":"The template has the **minimum required fields** (`identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `author`, `tags`) but has a few issues before publishing:\n\n**Problems:**\n1. **Missing `$schema`** — Add `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for validation and editor support.\n2. **`Framework` symbol has no `replaces`** — The parameter is defined but never substitutes anything in the output files. You likely need `\"replaces\": \"net9.0\"` (or a matching placeholder) so the chosen framework actually gets applied.\n3. **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Recommended for NuGet so the template engine can group/version templates properly (e.g., `\"groupIdentity\": \"MyCompany.WebApi.CSharp\"`).\n\n**Nice-to-haves:**\n- `preferNameDirectory: true` — standard for project templates.\n- `defaultName` — fallback project name if none is provided.\n\n**Verdict:** Not quite ready — the `Framework` symbol is effectively a no-op, which is likely a bug. Fix that and add `$schema` + `groupIdentity` at minimum.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d9a09145-b906-4a04-9916-cbd34cae4052","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I'll check against the .NET template engine schema requirements.\n\nIssues I see:\n\n1. **Missing `$schema`** — Not strictly required, but highly recommended for tooling/validation. The standard schema URL is `http://json.schemastore.org/template`.\n\n2. **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Recommended for NuGet packages, especially if you plan to have multiple templates or versions. Helps the template engine group related templates.\n\n3. **Missing `precedence`** — Not strictly required but useful when multiple versions of a template exist.\n\n4. **Missing `preferNameDirectory`** — Optional but useful.\n\n\n5. **Missing `defaultName`** — Optional, but useful.\n\nThe core required fields are all accounted for: `iden